      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 20
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S (996.2) is a superlative example of Zuffenhausen engineering, presented in showroom condition. Powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six featuring VarioCam Plus, the powerplant is mated to a precise G96/31 6-speed manual transaxle. Mechanical integrity is paramount; this unit has undergone a proactive IMS bearing retrofit and rear main seal replacement, with a recent borescope confirming zero cylinder wall scoring. The widebody chassis remains structurally rigid, benefiting from the factory Turbo-spec suspension geometry and four-piston monobloc Brembo calipers. The Arctic Silver Metallic finish exhibits exceptional depth with no measurable paint correction required, while the interior retains its factory-fresh matte finish on all switchgear. Riding on staggered 18-inch Turbo-twist alloys with fresh N-rated Michelin Pilot Sport tires, this C4S offers a tactile, analog driving experience that is increasingly rare.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
